getDataType

public AttributeDataType getDataType()
Returns the data type of the attribute. This property is mandatory when creating a new attribute definition. By default, this property is set to AttributeDataType.CHAR

Returns:
the data type of the attribute

getDisplayLength

public int getDisplayLength()
Returns the display length (in characters) of the attribute. This property is mandatory when creating a new attribute definition. By default, this property is set to 25.

Returns:
the display length (in characters) of the attribute

getPendingDisplay

public boolean getPendingDisplay()
Returns whether the attribute can be configured to be visible to pending GUI displays. This property is mandatory when creating a new attribute definition. By default this property is set to true.

Returns:
true/false

getVisible

public boolean getVisible()

Returns:
true/false

getNumber

public int getNumber()
Returns the number of the attribute. This property is optional when creating a new attribute definition. If this property is not set, a free attribute number is allocated to this attribute definition.

the number of the attribute
